																		Author Commentary! (Written Entirely in the Imperial Tongue! (And then translated into English!))
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227600" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;" >Ihp</a></span> <span class="odate time_1395102876 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Mar 2014 00:34</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1993360">
									

<p>I've wanted to write for the AE Canon for a while now, but for some reason, it never came through. My original plan was for S &amp; C Plastics to cross over with this by having a pair of Imperials come to Site 87 and be pestered by Tristan Bailey, but I never was able to write up an ending for that. Plus, the names, man. The names are too god-damn complex.</p>
<p>Tom was sent to the Empire back in 2010, and became commissioner in 2011. Since then, he alternates between living at Site-1483 on the baseline and living in the imperial city, and quite frankly, he prefers the city. It's warmer there, usually, and the people are nice. He's wanted to come back to Sloth's Pit on occasion, but he's happy here. He might come back up for a family reunion at some point, though.</p>
<p>And Djoric: I'll stop writing your stuff better than you do when you write up the story bible for this canon! :3</p>

							</div>

								
					
